meta.description: Delta Air Lines Delta Sky Club at Hartsfield–Jackson Atlanta International Airport (ATL), Concourse C. Learn more about the lounge: amenities, photos, review, opening hours, location.

lounge.name: Delta Air Lines Delta Sky Club
lounge.description: The Delta Sky Club is an award-winning retreat that allows relaxation, productivity, or both.

reviews.content: Have to agree with the other reviews. This club is overcrowded and the food is always very picked over. Go to any other terminal.
Not Delta's best effort —Agree with other reviews; often crowded and buffet looks like a frat attacked it.
Better Sky Clubs in other concourses. Much smaller and less selection than the others. Worth it if you have a tight layover in C.
This lounge is tired. The front desk is bored. The food is picked over. The bartender is pissed off and stuck up. Shame on Delta.
Nice spread. Friendly folks. Smaller and not as many side tables by the comfy chairs. Quieter and darker (on a good way) atmosphere.

The staff is great, but it’s just a small lounge that’s a little crowded. Perfectly fine, but probably worth it to go to a different concourse if you have time. If not, enjoy the bar and small buffet!
It's clean, away from the masses and they have free beer and food. What more do I need? Oh, it's free because of my Platinum Card.
Quiet and fairly comfortable. No luxury amenities. Champagne is $12/glass unless you have a Delta credit card.
This lounge is nice, not very bright so there's a certain chill vibe, but it's almost always packed in here. Plenty of seats, but no area to sleep.
My favorite ATL Sky Club. While the food/snack/drinks offerings are really the same as other Sky Clubs, this one looks and feels nicer. Plenty of seating varieties and some great views.
Nice clean modern lounge. Friendly with some nice snack options.
Always packed! It's a bit sad and depressing compared to the lounge at Concourse F.
Great little hangout if you're looking to burn some time. Small but cozy.

Everything is pretty good here. As a Delta lounge in ATL, it is obviously busy, but it has never felt full to me (yet). Food isn't bad. My only complaint is you have to go to the bartender to get soda.
Smallish and also less "space-age" feel than other renovated clubs. Darker and more "refined" feel. Some nooks that are quieter to the right of desk when you walk in.
Breakfast spread included cereal, oatmeal, fruit, and hard boiled eggs. Seating was comfortable. High ceilings, natural lighting, decent view from windows. Only a few TVs. Quiet.
Nice new spread of afternoon salad and soups. Friendly and much less crowded than it used to be. Worth the upgrade.
Plenty of seating, friendly staff, looks great!
If it were a little bigger, and had showers, it would get four stars. Very nice place. Pleasant, upscale decor and leather (fairly comfy) chairs make it one of the better ATL lounges.

Though the renovation is nicely redone, the lounge is still on the smaller end. The free drinks are nice, and can be enjoyed along with decent snacks on comfy seats. However, don't expect any service.
This lounge has lofty ceilings and plenty of natural light. There are also plenty of seating in various forms: table, bar top, couch, etc.
